OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1774828709
OL,3,CScreen time for under-fives should be
OL,4,Climited to an hour a day, government
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FThe guidance to parents on screen time
OL,8,Ffor two to five-year-olds will advise
OL,9,Fthem to "try to keep it to one hour a
OL,10,Fday. Less if possible."
OL,12,FFor the screen time that two to five-
OL,13,Fyear-olds do have, families will be
OL,14,Fadvised to avoid fast-paced social
OL,15,Fmedia style videos and toys or tools
OL,16,Fthat use AI.
OL,18,FBedtimes and mealtimes should be
OL,19,Fscreen-free, with families advised to
OL,20,Finstead try background music, table
OL,21,Fgames, bedtime stories, and colouring.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
